{"article_id":"WmWroXhiu0DCmKNE","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Trump is edging out Democrat frontrunners Sen. Elizabeth Warren","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"( D-MA )","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"and Joe Biden","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"( D )","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"in head to head matchups in the Hawkeye State ,","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"Iowa Emerson College poll results","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"released this week show .","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"The poll","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"- taken October 13-16 , 2019 , among 888 registered voters in Iowa -","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"showed the president leading both Warren and Biden in hypothetical general election matchups in Iowa ,","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"besting both candidates 51 percent to 49 percent .","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"Sen. Bernie Sanders","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"( I-VT ) ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"however , appeared to hold an advantage in a hypothetical matchup ,","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"leading the president by two points- 51 percent to Trump ' s 49 percent .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"The margin of error is +/-3.2 percent ,","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"indicating that the race is in flux :","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"Sanders ' lead against the president comes","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"in spite of the fact","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"that he is not leading the Democrat field in the Hawkeye State .","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"Rather , Warren and Biden are tied with 23 percent support each ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"followed by Mayor Pete Buttigieg","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"( D ) ,","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"who garnered 16 percent support .","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"Sanders fell to fourth place with 13 percent support ,","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"followed by Andrew Yang","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"( D ) ,","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"Gov . Steve Bullock","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"( D ) ,","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"and Sen. Cory Booker","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"( D-NJ )","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"with five percent , four percent , and three percent , respectively .","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"The results outlined the most trouble for Sen. Kamala Harris","depth":5},{"id":33,"text":"( D-CA ) ,","depth":5},{"id":34,"text":"who has tried to revive her floundering campaign","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"by focusing on Iowa .","depth":5},{"id":36,"text":"Harris signaled a switch in campaign strategies in September ,","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"telling a colleague","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"that she is \" f * cking moving to Iowa. \"","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"\" ' I ' m f * cking moving to Iowa '","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"- Kamala Harris , \"","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"read an email","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"following the presidential hopeful ' s quip .","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"\" She cut to the chase ! \"","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"the email stated .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"\" We ' re doubling our organizers on the ground in Iowa","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"and Kamala is ramping up her time on the trail there ,","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"beginning today in Cedar Rapids. \"","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"The following month , Harris launched her \" I feel your pain \" tour across Iowa ,","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"which featured the presidential hopeful","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"speaking to Iowans in more \" intimate \" settings ,","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"even helping some \" prepare Sunday suppers . \"","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"Despite those efforts ,","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"she was only able to garner two percent support in the state , alongside Rep. Tulsi Gabbard","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"( D-HI )","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"and Tom Steyer","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"( D ) :","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"The poll also showed","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"that more Iowans oppose impeachment","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"than support it ,","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"48 percent to 42 percent :","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"IOWA POLL :","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"Do you support or oppose # Impeachment of @ realDonaldTrump ?","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"48 % Oppose","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"Impeachment does not appear to be a top priority among Iowans across the board ,","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"with only six percent considering it an important factor","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"in choosing whom to support for president .","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"Thirty-three percent said","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"the economy ,","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"19 percent said","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"health care ,","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"and ten percent chose \" social issues . \"","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"\" The Democrats have some work to do in Iowa convincing voters","depth":4},{"id":73,"text":"that impeachment is a top priority of Congress ;","depth":4},{"id":74,"text":"67 % of Democrats in Iowa support impeaching the president ,","depth":4},{"id":75,"text":"but only 10 % identify it as the most important issue","depth":5},{"id":76,"text":"in deciding their vote for president , \"","depth":5},{"id":77,"text":"Emerson Polling Director Spencer Kimball said .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":155,"left":149,"right":154,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":109,"right":148,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":109,"left":84,"right":108,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":84,"left":82,"right":83,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":82,"left":79,"right":81,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":79,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":81,"left":80,"right":4,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":80,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":83,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":108,"left":87,"right